<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=1367&amp;p=7070#p7070"><![CDATA[
What Jcee said. When Classic Start Menu is installed on Windows 8.1, you can configure it from Start Menu settings -&gt; Controls tab to make Microsoft's Start button open the Classic Menu or make it open Metro (Start screen). If you go to the Windows 8.1 Settings tab and set &quot;Disable active corners&quot; to 'None', then you can still open the Start screen with the bottom left hot corner and open the menu by clicking the button. So basically, any combination you want, it's extremely customizable.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=54">Gaurav</a> — Mon Oct 07, 2013 10:38 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
